  "local_port": 45714,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there a Monster Hunter PC game?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several **Monster Hunter** games available for PC! Capcom has expanded the **Monster Hunter** series beyond its traditional console platforms, making these popular titles accessible to PC gamers. Here are the key **Monster Hunter** games you can play on PC:\n\n### **1. Monster Hunter: World**\n- **Release Date:** January 26, 2018 (PC version)\n- **Description:** This installment significantly broadened the appeal of the series with its expansive open-world environments and enhanced graphics. It introduced seamless maps and more dynamic ecosystems, making monster hunting more immersive than ever.\n- **Availability:** Available on [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/app/582010/MONSTER_HUNTER_WORLD/) and the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/monster-hunter-world/9nblggh5hcnl).\n\n### **2. Monster Hunter World: Iceborne**\n- **Release Date:** September 6, 2019 (PC version)\n- **Description:** This major expansion for **Monster Hunter: World** adds new monsters, locales, and gameplay mechanics, including an advanced Master Rank with tougher challenges and deeper content.\n- **Availability:** Bundled with the base game on [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/app/582010/MONSTER_HUNTER_WORLD/) and the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/monster-hunter-world/9nblggh5hcnl).\n\n### **3. Monster Hunter Rise**\n- **Release Date:** January 12, 2022 (PC port, originally for Nintendo Switch in 2021)\n- **Description:** Building upon the success of previous titles, **Monster Hunter Rise** introduces new mechanics like the Wirebug and Palamute companions. It features a vibrant setting inspired by Japanese folklore, offering both single-player and multiplayer experiences.\n- **Availability:** Available on [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/app/1446780/Monster_Hunter_Rise/) and the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/monster-hunter-rise/9nblggh3k3p0).\n\n### **4. Monster Hunter Rise: Sunbreak**\n- **Release Date:** June 30, 2022 (PC version)\n- **Description:** This expansion adds new quests, monsters, and areas to explore, further enhancing the **Monster Hunter Rise** experience.\n- **Availability:** Available as DLC on [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/app/1646850/Monster_Hunter_Rise__Sunbreak/) and the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/monster-hunter-rise-sunbreak/9nzfbh2nk2b0).\n\n### **5. Monster Hunter Stories 2: Wings of Ruin**\n- **Release Date:** July 8, 2021 (PC version)\n- **Description:** A spin-off that offers a different take on the **Monster Hunter** universe, focusing on turn-based combat and story-driven gameplay. Players can hatch and bond with monsters, embarking on unique adventures.\n- **Availability:** Available on [Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/app/1638970/Monster_Hunter_Stories_2_Wings_of_Ruin/) and the [Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/monster-hunter-stories-2-wings-of-ruin/9nblggh3gmpb).\n\n### **Where to Buy:**\n- **[Steam](https://store.steampowered.com/):** Most **Monster Hunter** PC games are available here. You can purchase, download, and manage your games through the Steam client.\n- **[Microsoft Store](https://www.microsoft.com/store/productId/9NVFBH2NK2B0):** Some titles are also available through Microsoft's platform, which can be accessed directly on Windows 10 and 11 PCs.\n\n### **System Requirements:**\nBefore purchasing, make sure your PC meets the minimum system requirements for the game you\u2019re interested in. Here\u2019s a general idea:\n\n**Monster Hunter: World (Example Minimum Requirements):**\n- **OS:** Windows 10 (64-bit)\n- **Processor:** Intel Core i5-4460 | AMD FX-6300\n- **Memory:** 8 GB RAM\n- **Graphics:** NVIDIA GeForce GTX 760 | AMD Radeon R9 280\n- **DirectX:** Version 11\n- **Storage:** 43 GB available space\n\n*Note: Requirements vary between titles and expansions, so always check the specific requirements for each game.*\n\n### **Additional Features:**\n- **Cross-Platform Play:** Some titles support cross-play between PC and consoles, allowing you to hunt with friends regardless of their platform.\n- **Mods and Community Content:** PC players often enjoy a variety of user-created mods that can enhance or customize their gaming experience (though it's essential to use mods responsibly to avoid issues with game stability or violations of terms of service).\n\n### **Conclusion:**\nPC gamers have robust options within the **Monster Hunter** series, enjoying both core titles and spin-offs with rich content and engaging gameplay. Whether you're a seasoned hunter or new to the franchise, the PC platform offers a versatile and immersive way to dive into hunting mighty monsters.\n\nIf you have any specific questions about a particular game or need further assistance, feel free to ask!",
